			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was in a group last night in Storms and had a majority of my group argue with me when I said CoH cleared aggro if the person is far enough away when called.
<br />

<br />
Warrior trys to pull a desert giant and gets 6 of them...
<br />

<br />
Magician (me) says, "Keep running, I'll CoH you to clear aggro."
<br />
Cleric says, "CoH does not wipe aggro at all. I know this for fact. Don't CoH him or you'll kill us all"
<br />
Magician2 says, "CoH doesn't affect aggro anymore, they nerfed it awhile ago."
<br />
Warrior says, "CoH doesn't clear aggro, it just lowers it."
<br />

<br />
Now, I got into a little heated debate about it with them, mainly because they decided they knew my spells better then I do. I know there was a CoH change not long after it went live that put a distance factor, but I don't remember any other changes since, other than restricting it everywhere. Am I wrong??</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
