				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The measuring device I use is Malosini.  I am not 100% sure what distance is important.  Is it how far the target of the CoH is away from the mage when the spell hits?  Or is it how far the target of the CoH ends up from the mob(s) that are mad when the spell hits?
<br />

<br />
I go with the "better safe than sorry" approach.  If the target is far enough away from you that most likely means he is going to be pulled a long way away from the mob also.  If the target is too far for you to be able to cast Malosini on, I have never had aggro remain after the CoH.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=103898" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Evelle Fyrestrike</a>
