			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">From personal experience in PoS and Bot(lower towers):
<br />

<br />
I hunt alot with a group, where a warrior is our puller.  CoH works great in both places.  If the puller gets more than we can handle, he runs away from us and hits his CoH Me hotkey.  On potential wipes, I have even backed up, while my pet was still fighting, and cohed clerics out of agrro range, when they were trying to camp, but couldn't, because of getting hit.
<br />

<br />
Little secret here: CoH also works great for splitting the bees in PoS.  Puller goes into the trees and pulls out 3 or 4 bees.  He runs off, and tagger tries to pull one off him, first puller gets cohed.  Tagger, depending on how many he pulled off first puller, either brings it in, or he yells for a coh, and the first puller tags off him.  We call it CoH splitting, and it works really well, if you don't have a fd puller, who can split adds himself.  FD pullers die more than a warrior puller using coh splitting.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
